cpNode i/o tester. When testing a new or repaired cpNode or IOX[16|32] you want a 
convenient set of push buttons to ground the inputs and check that outputs are drive high (or low).
The board has 8 "tactile" switches and pair of feamle headers for commodity 8 position common-anode 
or common cathode displays. Common can be selected as 5v or ground with Berg jumpers.

The board snaps into the 7CM Tyco snap track we (MRCS) use for the cpNode and IOX boards, so everything
stays in place while you test. Male headers are provided for 8 position Dupont jumpers to connect to the
board(s) under test.
